  <h2><a href="../../node/32" title="Performance tuning and optimization of high traffic Drupal sites">Performance tuning and optimization of high traffic Drupal sites</a></h2>

  
  <div class="content">
    <div class="field field-type-text field-field-room"><div class="field-label">Room:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item odd">BA 1240</div></div></div><p>You have a Drupal site, and it is successful. Perhaps too successful. First your shared hosting sends you notice that you are "exceeding resources". Then you go up a notch to a VPS. Then your site gets on Digg, and it dies.</p>
<p>Now what?</p>
<p>Is it time to find another host? Move up to dedicated hosting? </p>
<p>Perhaps just tuning and optimization is necessary.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="clear-block clear">
    <div class="meta">
          <div class="terms"><ul class="links inline"><li  class="first taxonomy_term_4"><a href="4" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_4">Consultants</a></li>
