<div id="node-10" class="node">


  <h2><a href="../../node/10" title="Mass Site Management on the Drupal Platform">Mass Site Management on the Drupal Platform</a></h2>

  
  <div class="content">
    <div class="field field-type-text field-field-room"><div class="field-label">Room:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item odd">BA 1240</div></div></div><p><strong>UPDATE:</strong> Slides are available <a href="http://anarres.ca/blog/drupalcamptoronto">here</a> (or <a href="http://2007.drupalcamptoronto.org/sites/drupalcamptoronto.org/files/dct2-mass-site-management.tgz">right here</a> onsite)</p>
<p>Drupal's "multisite" capabilities are relatively well-known at this point, and quite easy to use.  We will briefly go over how this works, but quickly move into more "advanced" usage of this important feature of the Drupal framework.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="clear-block clear">
    <div class="meta">
